"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: LLM-Generated Trail Titles & Descriptions (Agent-Aware)\n\n## Context\n\nParts A (checkpoints.json) and B (prompt-based titles) are already implemented and passing CI. However, `titleFromPrompt()` just truncates the first line of the user's prompt, producing mediocre titles. The user wants an LLM to generate proper trail titles and descriptions from the session transcript.\n\nThis happens **at first condensation** (PostCommit) because:\n- Rich context available (prompts + transcript + files touched)\n- Only once per trail (first commit)\n- No concurrency issues (synchronous in hook process)\n\n**Agent-aware**: Not all agents have non-interactive CLI modes. Claude Code has `claude --print`, but Gemini CLI and OpenCode don't. We add an optional `TextGenerator` interface that agents implement when capable, and skip title generation for agents that can't.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### C1. Add `TextGenerator` optional interface to agent package\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`\n\nAdd alongside other optional interfaces (`TranscriptAnalyzer`, `HookSupport`, etc.):\n\n```go\n// TextGenerator is an optional interface for agents whose CLI supports\n// non-interactive text generation (e.g., claude --print).\n// Used for AI-powered metadata generation (trail titles, summaries).\ntype TextGenerator interface {\n    // GenerateText sends a prompt to the agent's CLI and returns the raw text response.\n    // model is a hint (e.g., \"haiku\", \"sonnet\"). Implementations may ignore if not applicable.\n    GenerateText(ctx context.Context, prompt string, model string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n### C2. Implement `TextGenerator` for Claude Code\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/generate.go` (new file)\n\n```go\npackage claudecode\n\nfunc (c *ClaudeCodeAgent) GenerateText(ctx context.Context, prompt string, model string) (string, error) {\n    claudePath := \"claude\"\n    if model == \"\" {\n        model = \"haiku\"\n    }\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, claudePath,\n        \"--print\", \"--output-format\", \"json\",\n        \"--model\", model, \"--setting-sources\", \"\")\n    cmd.Dir = os.TempDir()\n    cmd.Env = stripGitEnv(os.Environ())\n    cmd.Stdin = strings.NewReader(prompt)\n    // Execute, parse {\"result\": \"...\"} envelope, return result string\n}\n```\n\nIncludes a local `stripGitEnv()` helper (same 7-line function as in `summarize/claude.go` — simple filter of `GIT_*` env vars; not worth extracting to a shared package for this).\n\n### C3. Refactor existing `ClaudeGenerator` to use `TextGenerator`\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/claude.go`\n\nUpdate `ClaudeGenerator.Generate()` to use `TextGenerator` interface when available, preserving the existing `CommandRunner` injection for tests:\n\n```go\nfunc (g *ClaudeGenerator) Generate(ctx context.Context, input Input) (*checkpoint.Summary, error) {\n    transcriptText := FormatCondensedTranscript(input)\n    prompt := buildSummarizationPrompt(transcriptText)\n\n    // Use TextGenerator if available (allows agent-aware generation)\n    if g.TextGen != nil {\n        rawResult, err := g.TextGen.GenerateText(ctx, prompt, g.Model)\n        // parse rawResult as checkpoint.Summary JSON\n    }\n\n    // Fallback to direct CLI invocation (for tests with CommandRunner)\n    // ... existing implementation ...\n}\n```\n\nActually, this refactor adds complexity for marginal benefit. **Simpler approach**: Leave `ClaudeGenerator` as-is (it works, tests pass). The new trail title code directly uses the `TextGenerator` interface from the agent. The two code paths (summarize `ClaudeGenerator` for checkpoint summaries, `TextGenerator` for trail titles) share the same underlying Claude CLI but through different layers.\n\n**Decision**: Skip this refactor. Keep `ClaudeGenerator` unchanged. Trail title generation uses `TextGenerator` directly.\n\n### C4. New file: `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/trail_title.go`\n\nTrail title/description generation, agent-aware:\n\n```go\npackage summarize\n\nconst trailTitlePromptTemplate = `Analyze this development session transcript and generate a title and description.\n\n<transcript>\n%s\n</transcript>\n\nReturn a JSON object:\n{\n  \"title\": \"Short imperative title (max 80 chars)\",\n  \"description\": \"1-3 sentence description of what was accomplished and why\"\n}\n\nGuidelines:\n- Title: imperative mood, captures core intent (e.g. \"Add user authentication flow\")\n- Description: explain the \"what\" and \"why\", not the \"how\"\n- Return ONLY the JSON object`\n\nconst trailTitleModel = \"haiku\"\n\ntype TrailTitleResult struct {\n    Title       string `json:\"title\"`\n    Description string `json:\"description\"`\n}\n\nfunc GenerateTrailTitle(ctx context.Context, transcriptBytes []byte, filesTouched []string, agentType agent.AgentType) (*TrailTitleResult, error) {\n    // 1. Get the active agent and check if it implements TextGenerator\n    ag, err := agent.GetByAgentType(agentType)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"agent not found: %w\", err)\n    }\n    gen, ok := ag.(agent.TextGenerator)\n    if !ok {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"agent %s does not support text generation\", agentType)\n    }\n\n    // 2. Build condensed transcript (reuse existing infrastructure)\n    condensed, err := BuildCondensedTranscriptFromBytes(transcriptBytes, agentType)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    input := Input{Transcript: condensed, FilesTouched: filesTouched}\n    transcriptText := FormatCondensedTranscript(input)\n\n    // 3. Build prompt and call agent's TextGenerator\n    prompt := fmt.Sprintf(trailTitlePromptTemplate, transcriptText)\n    rawResult, err := gen.GenerateText(ctx, prompt, trailTitleModel)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    // 4. Parse JSON response\n    cleaned := extractJSONFromMarkdown(rawResult)\n    var result TrailTitleResult\n    if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(cleaned), &result); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse trail title JSON: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return &result, nil\n}\n```\n\n### C5. Add `Transcript` field to `CondenseResult`\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go`\n\n```go\ntype CondenseResult struct {\n    ...existing fields...\n    Transcript []byte // Raw transcript bytes for downstream consumers\n}\n```\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\n\nIn `CondenseSession()` return (~line 250), add: `Transcript: sessionData.Transcript,`\n\n### C6. Add `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript` helper\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\n\n```go\nfunc generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo *git.Repository, branchName string, transcript []byte, filesTouched []string, agentType agent.AgentType) {\n    if !settings.IsSummarizeEnabled() {\n        return\n    }\n    store := trail.NewStore(repo)\n    existing, err := store.FindByBranch(branchName)\n    if err != nil || existing == nil {\n        return\n    }\n    // Only generate once: skip if description already set\n    if existing.Description != \"\" {\n        return\n    }\n    logCtx := logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), \"trail-title\")\n    result, err := summarize.GenerateTrailTitle(logCtx, transcript, filesTouched, agentType)\n    if err != nil {\n        logging.Debug(logCtx, \"trail title generation skipped\",\n            slog.String(\"error\", err.Error()))\n        return\n    }\n    //nolint:errcheck // best-effort: trail title generation is non-critical\n    store.Update(existing.TrailID, func(m *trail.Metadata) {\n        if result.Title != \"\" {\n            m.Title = result.Title\n        }\n        if result.Description != \"\" {\n            m.Description = result.Description\n        }\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### C7. Wire into `condenseAndUpdateState` (manual-commit)\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\n\nIn `condenseAndUpdateState()`, after the existing `appendCheckpointToTrail()` call (~line 825):\n\n```go\n// Generate trail title/description from transcript (best-effort, first condensation only)\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\nif branchName != \"\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) {\n    generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo, branchName, result.Transcript, result.FilesTouched, state.AgentType)\n}\n```\n\n### C8. Wire into `SaveStep` (auto-commit)\n\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go`\n\nIn `SaveStep()`, after the existing `appendCheckpointToTrail()` call (~line 166):\n\n```go\n// Generate trail title/description (best-effort, first condensation only)\nbranchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\nif branchName != \"\" && branchName != GetDefaultBranchName(repo) && ctx.TranscriptPath != \"\" {\n    if transcriptData, readErr := os.ReadFile(ctx.TranscriptPath); readErr == nil {\n        filesTouched := mergeFilesTouched(nil, ctx.ModifiedFiles, ctx.NewFiles, ctx.DeletedFiles)\n        generateTrailTitleFromTranscript(repo, branchName, transcriptData, filesTouched, ctx.AgentType)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Files Summary\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` | Add `TextGenerator` optional interface |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/generate.go` | **New**: Implement `TextGenerator` for Claude Code |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/summarize/trail_title.go` | **New**: `GenerateTrailTitle()`, prompt template, `TrailTitleResult` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` | Add `Transcript []byte` to `CondenseResult` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Populate `Transcript` in `CondenseResult` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Add `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()`, wire after condensation |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go` | Wire `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()` after save |\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n1. **`TextGenerator` optional interface** — follows existing pattern (like `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `HookSupport`). Agents opt in when their CLI supports non-interactive generation. Claude Code implements it today; Gemini/OpenCode can add it later.\n2. **Haiku model** — trail titles are simple; haiku is fast (~1-2s) and cheap\n3. **One-time gate** — `Description != \"\"` ensures LLM is only called on first condensation per trail\n4. **Settings gate** — reuses `settings.IsSummarizeEnabled()`; no new setting\n5. **Graceful skip** — if agent doesn't implement `TextGenerator`, title stays as prompt-derived; no error shown to user\n6. **No `ClaudeGenerator` refactor** — existing summarize code works; trail titles use `TextGenerator` directly\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nManual test:\n1. Create a branch, enable entire with `summarize.enabled: true`\n2. Run a Claude Code session, make a commit\n3. Check `entire trail` output — should show LLM-generated title and description\n4. Make a second commit — title should NOT be regenerated (description already set)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/dip/.claude/projects/-Users-dip-Repositories-cli/6edd18ba-782c-4019-88d9-018079feea08.jsonl"